            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Sanatan Dharma, often referred to as Hinduism, is one of the world's oldest religions with a rich and diverse history.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Ancient Origins</h2>
            <p>Sanatan Dharma traces its roots to the ancient Indus Valley civilization and the Vedas, the oldest sacred texts.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Development of Philosophical Schools</h2>
            <p>Over time, various philosophical schools, such as Advaita Vedanta and Yoga, emerged within Sanatan Dharma.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Medieval Period</h2>
            <p>During the medieval period, the religion saw the rise of Bhakti and Sufi movements, influencing its devotional aspects.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Modern Era</h2>
            <p>In the modern era, Sanatan Dharma has spread globally, with millions of followers around the world.</p>
